i disabled Windows support at the initial commit just because i haven't got the bandwidth to test it on Windows.
So what is the expectation of Windows support? Make it functional will be enough or make it as performant as Linux?

body:
@yf225 [mkldnn](https://github.com/intel/mkl-dnn#system-requirements) has Windows support, you can use MSVS compiler, icc is not needed there.

i disabled Windows support at the initial commit just because i haven't got the bandwidth to test it on Windows.

So what is the expectation of Windows support? Make it functional will be enough or make it as performant as Linux?
